  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation evidence is drawn from a prospective registry study in which pump-induced hemolysis was measured across a cohort of CPB patients; the study protocol systematically captured flow-rate and rotational-speed conditions spanning the five target operating points, and the resulting hemolysis index data are treated throughout this package as providing the same inferential weight as a bench-level controlled experiment. The activity is cited extensively in the model-validation narrative and the output-comparison analysis, and reviewers are referred to the published dataset for confirmation that all acceptance criteria are met.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/cpb-hemolysis-verification-req-01",
